						<div class="postbody">Mapper 7 should not have CHR ROM. All CHR data should be stored in PRG ROM and copied to CHR RAM at runtime. The header says the file should be exactly 262160 bytes; is this true?
<br />
<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Do modern PCs do this anyways?</div>
<br />You're not making a program to run on "modern PCs". You're making a program to run on a Nintendo Entertainment System. At power on, the contents of the internal RAM aren't predictable. Clearing everything helps define the environment in which your program runs.</div>

