				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Your code seems correct, I think your problem is the palette. You have set the first color to white but all others to black. The thing is that some other colors map to the same phisical address as the first color, so you are replacing the white with black, so you only see black.
<br />
<br />Change you palette to:
<br />
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">palette:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;.db $30,$0f,$0f,$0f, $30,$0f,$0f,$0f, $30,$0f,$0f,$0f, $30,$0f,$0f,$0f<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;.db $30,$0f,$0f,$0f, $30,$0f,$0f,$0f, $30,$0f,$0f,$0f, $30,$0f,$0f,$0f</div>
<br />And you should see something.
<br />
<br />EDIT: found the <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=21418#21418" class="postlink">post</a> saying what palette slots are mirrors. So when you wrote black to $3F10 you replaced the white at $3F00.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

